ğŸ¯ Goal:

Create a page that allows anyone to search for found documents by document type or number, and display the results from the database.

ğŸªœ Step 1: Create a New File

Inside your main project folder (lost_document_tracker/),
create a new file named:

search_found.php

ğŸªœ Step 2: Add This Code
<?php include('includes/db_connect.php'); ?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Search Found Documents</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h2>Search Found Documents</h2>

  <form method="GET" action="">
    <label>Search by Document Type or Number:</label><br>
    <input type="text" name="search" placeholder="Enter document type or number..." required>
    <button type="submit">Search</button>
  </form>

  <hr>

  <?php
  if (isset($_GET['search'])) {
      $search = $_GET['search'];
      $sql = "SELECT * FROM found_documents 
              WHERE doc_type LIKE '%$search%' 
              OR doc_number LIKE '%$search%'
              ORDER BY date DESC";

      $result = $conn->query($sql);

      if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
          echo "<table border='1' cellpadding='10'>
                  <tr>
                    <th>ID</th>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Document Type</th>
                    <th>Document Number</th>
                    <th>Contact</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                    <th>Date</th>
                  </tr>";

          while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
              echo "<tr>
                      <td>{$row['id']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['name']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['doc_type']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['doc_number']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['contact']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['description']}</td>
                      <td>{$row['date']}</td>
                    </tr>";
          }

          echo "</table>";
      } else {
          echo "<p style='color:red;'>No documents found for '$search'.</p>";
      }
  }
  ?>
</body>
</html>

ğŸªœ Step 3: Test in Browser

